1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,000
[English subtitles are available]

2
00:01:36,350 --> 00:01:42,229
[I Don't Want to Be Friends With You]

3
00:01:42,570 --> 00:01:47,570
[Episode 15: Start Over
in a Daunting Way]

4
00:01:49,530 --> 00:01:51,520
Li Qing Tong, we're running late.

5
00:01:51,610 --> 00:01:52,750
I'm coming.

6
00:01:53,650 --> 00:01:54,759
Are all the snacks packed?

7
00:01:54,840 --> 00:01:55,600
Yes.

8
00:01:55,690 --> 00:01:56,870
Where is your bag?

9
00:01:57,650 --> 00:01:58,490
My bag.

10
00:01:58,570 --> 00:01:59,320
Bag.

11
00:01:59,410 --> 00:02:00,680
Hurry up.

12
00:02:00,770 --> 00:02:01,950
I'm coming.

13
00:02:07,050 --> 00:02:09,949
Ladies, where do you get off?

14
00:02:22,410 --> 00:02:23,990
Why do you all sit over there?

15
00:02:24,210 --> 00:02:24,600
Xiao, come here.

16
00:02:24,690 --> 00:02:25,570
Come here.

17
00:02:26,170 --> 00:02:27,440
Just sit there by yourself.

18
00:02:27,520 --> 00:02:28,600
Be a man.

19
00:02:28,690 --> 00:02:29,040
You...

20
00:02:29,130 --> 00:02:29,410
You...

21
00:02:29,490 --> 00:02:31,079
We can hang out together finally.

22
00:02:31,170 --> 00:02:32,140
Yes.

23
00:02:34,970 --> 00:02:35,760
Have you all

24
00:02:35,850 --> 00:02:36,950
estimated your scores?

25
00:02:38,010 --> 00:02:39,090
Are you crazy?

26
00:02:39,170 --> 00:02:40,160
We rarely get the chance to travel.

27
00:02:40,250 --> 00:02:42,310
Can you stop talking about
such a depressing thing?

28
00:02:42,650 --> 00:02:43,840
I brought the answer keys.

29
00:02:43,930 --> 00:02:44,960
Let's check the answers later.

30
00:02:45,050 --> 00:02:45,560
Hurry up.

31
00:02:45,650 --> 00:02:47,920
If you want to estimate scores, can
you go to the next compartment?

32
00:02:48,010 --> 00:02:48,450
That is.

33
00:02:48,530 --> 00:02:49,740
You guys are so annoying.

34
00:02:50,770 --> 00:02:52,380
Put them away.

35
00:02:52,690 --> 00:02:53,040
Listen,

36
00:02:53,130 --> 00:02:53,560
during this trip,

37
00:02:53,650 --> 00:02:56,320
no one is to mention anything about
the College Entrance Exam.

38
00:02:56,410 --> 00:02:58,310
You don't really fail the exam, do you?

39
00:02:59,690 --> 00:03:00,280
I tell you

40
00:03:00,370 --> 00:03:01,830
not to mention it.

41
00:03:02,650 --> 00:03:03,670
We should be happy

42
00:03:04,050 --> 00:03:06,350
when we travel.

43
00:03:06,450 --> 00:03:07,490
I gave a lot.

44
00:03:07,570 --> 00:03:09,660
Li Qing Tong, if you fail the exam,
you're done for.

45
00:03:10,050 --> 00:03:11,710
I'm sure I'll pass the exam.

46
00:03:11,890 --> 00:03:12,720
Forget about it.

47
00:03:12,810 --> 00:03:14,190
My fault.

48
00:03:14,280 --> 00:03:15,040
Let's

49
00:03:15,130 --> 00:03:16,170
have a good time first.

50
00:03:16,250 --> 00:03:17,870
We talk about the scores
after we get back.

51
00:03:19,690 --> 00:03:20,360
Li Qing Tong.

52
00:03:20,440 --> 00:03:21,950
Have you seen Wu Zhi Xun lately?

53
00:03:24,370 --> 00:03:25,430
No.

54
00:03:26,530 --> 00:03:27,950
Let me tell you something.

55
00:03:29,410 --> 00:03:30,810
Wu Zhi Xun really didn't take
the National College Entrance Exam.

56
00:03:30,890 --> 00:03:33,670
And he's been arguing with his dad.

57
00:03:33,850 --> 00:03:34,840
All the neighbours heard it.

58
00:03:34,930 --> 00:03:35,910
It's especially scary.

59
00:03:36,130 --> 00:03:37,000
Really?

60
00:03:37,090 --> 00:03:37,440
Yes.

61
00:03:37,530 --> 00:03:38,360
How do you know that?

62
00:03:38,450 --> 00:03:39,720
Qian told me.

63
00:03:39,800 --> 00:03:41,829
His house is next to Wu Zhi Xun's.

64
00:03:42,090 --> 00:03:42,920
Why do you gossip

65
00:03:43,010 --> 00:03:44,079
about others all day like a girl?

66
00:03:44,170 --> 00:03:44,560
I'm not a girl.

67
00:03:44,640 --> 00:03:45,329
You are a girl.

68
00:03:45,410 --> 00:03:46,210
I'm not a girl.

69
00:03:46,290 --> 00:03:46,800
Just you wait.

70
00:03:46,890 --> 00:03:47,160
I...

71
00:03:47,250 --> 00:03:48,290
I was asking for Li Qing Tong.

72
00:03:48,370 --> 00:03:49,120
She doesn't need it.

73
00:03:49,210 --> 00:03:49,730
She always went to Wu Zhi Xun's house

74
00:03:49,810 --> 00:03:51,790
to look for him at that time.

75
00:03:52,250 --> 00:03:53,880
I didn't look for him.

76
00:03:53,970 --> 00:03:54,950
I did not.

77
00:04:22,850 --> 00:04:23,950
Wu Zhi Xun.

78
00:04:24,360 --> 00:04:25,760
Are you there?

79
00:04:25,850 --> 00:04:27,310
Please open the door.

80
00:04:27,490 --> 00:04:28,980
I know you're at home.

81
00:04:30,810 --> 00:04:32,670
Whether you are home or not,

82
00:04:32,890 --> 00:04:34,700
there is something I must say to you.

83
00:04:34,890 --> 00:04:35,790
I know

84
00:04:35,950 --> 00:04:37,470
I should apologize to you.

85
00:04:37,810 --> 00:04:40,790
If I didn't ask you to tutor us,

86
00:04:41,050 --> 00:04:43,350
things wouldn't be like this.

87
00:04:43,450 --> 00:04:44,159
But

88
00:04:44,250 --> 00:04:45,680
you can't always hide from me.

89
00:04:45,770 --> 00:04:47,640
We are friends.

90
00:04:47,730 --> 00:04:50,070
How can you ignore your friend?

91
00:04:53,610 --> 00:04:55,550
They said you didn't take the
National College Entrance Exam.

92
00:04:55,770 --> 00:04:56,909
I don't believe that.

93
00:04:57,690 --> 00:04:59,670
If you have anything to say,

94
00:05:00,090 --> 00:05:01,950
you can tell me.

95
00:05:02,690 --> 00:05:03,790
I'll wait for you.

96
00:05:07,690 --> 00:05:08,950
Then I'm off.

97
00:05:21,130 --> 00:05:22,010
What the hell are you looking at?

98
00:05:22,930 --> 00:05:23,810
You're here.

99
00:05:25,290 --> 00:05:26,170
Sit to the side.

100
00:05:34,250 --> 00:05:35,190
What a coincidence.

101
00:05:37,010 --> 00:05:37,650
I do this on purpose.

102
00:05:37,730 --> 00:05:38,620
Not a coincidence at all.

103
00:05:39,010 --> 00:05:39,890
You're not with us,

104
00:05:40,010 --> 00:05:41,200
are you?

105
00:05:41,290 --> 00:05:41,860
I'm just with you guys.

106
00:05:41,950 --> 00:05:42,490
Who told you

107
00:05:42,570 --> 00:05:43,950
to come?

108
00:05:44,890 --> 00:05:45,950
He told me to come.

109
00:05:47,810 --> 00:05:48,680
The more the merrier.

110
00:05:48,770 --> 00:05:49,650
Right?

111
00:05:50,050 --> 00:05:51,320
Why didn't you tell me in advance?

112
00:05:51,409 --> 00:05:52,800
You should have
discussed this with me, right?

113
00:05:52,890 --> 00:05:54,120
It's too late.

114
00:05:54,210 --> 00:05:55,630
Please show me some respect.

115
00:05:56,250 --> 00:05:58,600
How nice to be out on
a trip with lots of boys.

116
00:05:58,690 --> 00:05:59,800
This is the way to be safe.

117
00:05:59,890 --> 00:06:00,400
Chen Jun He.

118
00:06:00,490 --> 00:06:01,320
You have to promise me.

119
00:06:01,410 --> 00:06:02,710
Stay out of trouble.

120
00:06:02,970 --> 00:06:04,670
Of course.

121
00:06:05,010 --> 00:06:06,230
Let's be happy.

122
00:06:06,510 --> 00:06:08,130
Everyone should have fun on the trip,

123
00:06:08,210 --> 00:06:09,090
right?

124
00:06:09,650 --> 00:06:10,200
Chen Jun He.

125
00:06:10,290 --> 00:06:11,510
Where's the stuff I asked you to bring?

126
00:06:15,890 --> 00:06:17,070
So much.

127
00:06:17,770 --> 00:06:19,110
Brother, you're so generous.

128
00:06:19,510 --> 00:06:19,960
Wait,

129
00:06:20,050 --> 00:06:22,270
you gave it all away.
There's nothing left for us.

130
00:06:22,510 --> 00:06:23,480
Let us have some.

131
00:06:23,570 --> 00:06:24,450
Let us...

132
00:06:28,330 --> 00:06:29,760
When did you become good friends with him?

133
00:06:29,850 --> 00:06:31,040
No discord, no concord.

134
00:06:31,130 --> 00:06:33,110
That's how simple friendship
between boys can be.

135
00:06:34,010 --> 00:06:35,470
You're a yes-man.

136
00:06:39,290 --> 00:06:40,280
I let him carry your stuff

137
00:06:40,370 --> 00:06:40,860
to avenge you,

138
00:06:40,950 --> 00:06:42,270
okay?

139
00:06:43,850 --> 00:06:44,730
Well.

140
00:06:45,210 --> 00:06:46,710
You are better.

141
00:06:49,170 --> 00:06:50,750
Enjoy yourself.

142
00:07:46,150 --> 00:07:47,030
Are we there?

143
00:07:52,110 --> 00:07:53,170
It's my turn.

144
00:07:53,750 --> 00:07:54,730
A pair of Jacks.

145
00:07:54,909 --> 00:07:55,340
A pair of Kings.

146
00:07:55,430 --> 00:07:57,290
A pair of Aces.

147
00:07:59,110 --> 00:08:00,780
I am wrong, and I only have one.

148
00:08:01,390 --> 00:08:02,490
Let me see.

149
00:08:03,190 --> 00:08:04,020
See what?

150
00:08:04,110 --> 00:08:05,260
See your own.

151
00:08:05,350 --> 00:08:06,930
Can you?

152
00:08:07,230 --> 00:08:08,360
A pair of Sixes. I'm done.

153
00:08:09,350 --> 00:08:10,560
Done?

154
00:08:11,350 --> 00:08:12,490
We won again.

155
00:08:13,390 --> 00:08:15,050
I have a pair of Aces.

156
00:08:15,590 --> 00:08:16,140
Is it?

157
00:08:16,230 --> 00:08:17,810
I may not have been
paying attention just now.

158
00:08:20,590 --> 00:08:21,260
Brother.

159
00:08:21,340 --> 00:08:23,250
Why don't you get involved?

160
00:08:23,510 --> 00:08:24,620
Give me all the cards.

161
00:08:24,710 --> 00:08:25,500
I have a strategy.

162
00:08:25,590 --> 00:08:28,290
I don't believe you.

163
00:08:28,710 --> 00:08:30,540
We are a team.

164
00:08:30,630 --> 00:08:31,860
We'll lose if we go on like this.

165
00:08:31,950 --> 00:08:32,620
I don't care.

166
00:08:32,710 --> 00:08:33,700
We have been losing anyway.

167
00:08:33,789 --> 00:08:34,380
One more time.

168
00:08:34,470 --> 00:08:35,230
That's it.

169
00:08:35,309 --> 00:08:37,210
You two are bad teammates.

170
00:08:37,470 --> 00:08:38,380
I don't want to be on
a team with you guys.

171
00:08:38,470 --> 00:08:39,570
I want to change teammates.

172
00:08:39,750 --> 00:08:40,730
I don't play anymore.

173
00:08:41,140 --> 00:08:42,179
We have arrived at Qingshui Station.

174
00:08:42,270 --> 00:08:43,340
We have arrived at Qingshui Station.

175
00:08:43,429 --> 00:08:44,380
Hurry up.

176
00:08:44,470 --> 00:08:45,580
Where are we going?

177
00:08:45,670 --> 00:08:46,550
Qingshui.

178
00:08:48,070 --> 00:08:48,950
Come on.

179
00:09:00,030 --> 00:09:00,780
Bag.

180
00:09:00,870 --> 00:09:02,660
Hurry up.

181
00:09:02,750 --> 00:09:03,460
Take it.

182
00:09:03,550 --> 00:09:04,970
Hurry up.

183
00:09:14,870 --> 00:09:15,980
Can we choose a more advanced

184
00:09:16,070 --> 00:09:17,690
mode of transportation in the future?

185
00:09:18,150 --> 00:09:19,450
This is lame.

186
00:09:20,030 --> 00:09:21,170
I like this.

187
00:09:21,300 --> 00:09:22,140
It's wild.

188
00:09:22,230 --> 00:09:22,660
Yeah.

189
00:09:22,750 --> 00:09:24,780
We can have a slap-up
meal with the money we save.

190
00:09:24,870 --> 00:09:26,010
What's wrong?

191
00:09:26,390 --> 00:09:27,710
There are many chickens,
ducks and geese here.

192
00:09:27,790 --> 00:09:29,350
We can still eat them.

193
00:09:29,430 --> 00:09:31,410
Don't hurt the animals.

194
00:09:35,110 --> 00:09:35,990
Brother.

195
00:09:36,190 --> 00:09:37,580
Why don't you say something?

196
00:09:37,670 --> 00:09:39,560
Or you are very much like a bodyguard.

197
00:09:41,150 --> 00:09:41,860
Have you all

198
00:09:41,950 --> 00:09:43,050
estimated your scores?

199
00:09:45,550 --> 00:09:47,340
Don't mention the National College
Entrance Exam, okay?

200
00:09:47,430 --> 00:09:49,290
I will be angry with whoever mentions
the National College Entrance Exam again.

201
00:10:12,830 --> 00:10:16,330
We've travelled a long way
for such a lame village?

202
00:10:17,070 --> 00:10:17,990
This is an ancient village.

203
00:10:18,070 --> 00:10:19,260
It's several hundred years old.

204
00:10:19,350 --> 00:10:20,460
You know nothing.

205
00:10:20,550 --> 00:10:21,220
That's it.

206
00:10:21,310 --> 00:10:23,170
It's really different from Tieyuan.

207
00:10:23,550 --> 00:10:24,540
There are so few people here.

208
00:10:24,630 --> 00:10:26,850
This is sure to be a popular
attraction in the future.

209
00:10:29,670 --> 00:10:31,600
There are chickens.

210
00:10:35,670 --> 00:10:38,490
Can we find a flatter road next time?

211
00:10:39,350 --> 00:10:41,010
You called me here to be a coolie.

212
00:10:45,020 --> 00:10:45,900
Ba Dan.

213
00:10:46,190 --> 00:10:47,250
Take it.

214
00:10:49,230 --> 00:10:50,110
What?

215
00:10:51,550 --> 00:10:52,310
Brother.

216
00:10:52,390 --> 00:10:54,210
You're a bit much.

217
00:11:05,270 --> 00:11:07,890
The air has a sense of freedom.

218
00:11:08,390 --> 00:11:09,810
It's better to grow up.

219
00:11:11,540 --> 00:11:12,380
Not right.

220
00:11:12,470 --> 00:11:14,180
When we go to college,
we will be separated.

221
00:11:14,270 --> 00:11:16,020
It's not good to grow up.

222
00:11:16,110 --> 00:11:17,700
Can't you enrol in the
same college as me?

223
00:11:17,790 --> 00:11:18,830
I want to.

224
00:11:18,910 --> 00:11:20,810
But my mum wants me to
go to college in the south.

225
00:11:21,030 --> 00:11:22,370
How about you come to
the same college with me?

226
00:11:23,750 --> 00:11:24,630
No.

227
00:11:25,430 --> 00:11:27,090
I don't want to be too
far away from my parents.

228
00:11:27,820 --> 00:11:28,260
How about you?

229
00:11:28,350 --> 00:11:29,230
Which college do you want to go to?

230
00:11:29,990 --> 00:11:31,150
I'll be with her.

231
00:11:31,230 --> 00:11:32,250
I have to take care of her.

232
00:11:32,750 --> 00:11:33,730
Come on.

233
00:11:33,830 --> 00:11:35,050
Hello, everyone.

234
00:11:35,190 --> 00:11:38,690
Today I will show you a
blindfolded watermelon cutting.

235
00:11:38,870 --> 00:11:40,050
Look.

236
00:11:48,150 --> 00:11:49,410
Where is the applause?

237
00:11:54,510 --> 00:11:55,650
How many watermelons do we buy?

238
00:11:57,470 --> 00:11:58,350
One.

239
00:12:02,230 --> 00:12:03,150
Wang Xiao Min.

240
00:12:03,230 --> 00:12:04,130
My fault.

241
00:12:08,110 --> 00:12:08,780
That's all your dishes.

242
00:12:08,860 --> 00:12:09,780
What would you like to drink?

243
00:12:09,870 --> 00:12:11,020
No, thanks.

244
00:12:11,110 --> 00:12:11,940
Well.

245
00:12:12,030 --> 00:12:13,170
Jin Bu, here.

246
00:12:17,310 --> 00:12:17,700
Is this tasty?

247
00:12:17,790 --> 00:12:19,230
We're all adults now.

248
00:12:19,310 --> 00:12:21,090
Shall we have some beer?

249
00:12:23,230 --> 00:12:24,700
Three beers, please.

250
00:12:24,790 --> 00:12:25,930
Six beers.

251
00:12:26,020 --> 00:12:27,290
You are so amazing.

252
00:12:27,550 --> 00:12:28,180
Take a box of beer,

253
00:12:28,270 --> 00:12:29,210
please.

254
00:12:31,350 --> 00:12:33,330
Cheers.

255
00:12:33,970 --> 00:12:35,470
[Ancient Village]

256
00:12:35,470 --> 00:12:36,540
The beer

257
00:12:36,630 --> 00:12:38,740
doesn't taste good.

258
00:12:38,830 --> 00:12:40,970
Why does my dad like drinking so much?

259
00:12:42,230 --> 00:12:43,780
Do we drink fake beer?

260
00:12:43,870 --> 00:12:45,740
Why is beer so addictive?

261
00:12:45,820 --> 00:12:47,740
Because it is our
first time drinking beer.

262
00:12:47,830 --> 00:12:49,780
Who cares if it's true or not?

263
00:12:49,870 --> 00:12:52,290
There are many things we
can't tell if they are true or not.

264
00:12:52,950 --> 00:12:55,140
I think the wine my uncle drinks is fake.

265
00:12:55,230 --> 00:12:57,420
He becomes suggestible

266
00:12:57,510 --> 00:12:58,890
after every drink.

267
00:13:00,510 --> 00:13:03,500
Can you give my dad a few
bottles of your uncle's wine?

268
00:13:03,590 --> 00:13:05,110
When my dad is drunk, he hits me.

269
00:13:05,190 --> 00:13:07,380
Your dad hits you even
when he isn't drunk.

270
00:13:07,470 --> 00:13:08,930
Well, that's true.

271
00:13:09,230 --> 00:13:10,660
But it's okay now.

272
00:13:10,750 --> 00:13:11,860
Even if my dad hits me,

273
00:13:11,950 --> 00:13:13,540
I don't feel any pain.

274
00:13:13,630 --> 00:13:15,640
It's because you've grown up.

275
00:13:16,030 --> 00:13:18,170
It's because they're getting old.

276
00:13:19,870 --> 00:13:22,680
We grow up in an instant.

277
00:13:24,590 --> 00:13:25,670
I still remember

278
00:13:25,750 --> 00:13:28,340
when I was a kid,

279
00:13:28,430 --> 00:13:30,100
I cried especially hard

280
00:13:30,190 --> 00:13:31,830
when I got lost with you two.

281
00:13:31,910 --> 00:13:32,460
When did this happen?

282
00:13:32,550 --> 00:13:33,810
I didn't know that.

283
00:13:35,310 --> 00:13:36,500
Well,

284
00:13:36,590 --> 00:13:38,140
twenty years from now,

285
00:13:38,230 --> 00:13:41,070
will we not remember the present either?

286
00:13:41,150 --> 00:13:42,610
As long as people are around,

287
00:13:42,700 --> 00:13:44,010
we can't forget.

288
00:13:45,550 --> 00:13:48,060
I remember the time Li Jin Bu kicked me.

289
